liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: After the most tumultuous of years, Spain has won their first Women's World Cup! Their players sink to the ground in joy. They're hugging each other and crying, as you would expect. La Roja were hugely impressive tonight - tremendous performance really. They controlled the majority of an incredibly high-quality game and repelled everything that England threw at them.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: SPAIN HAS WON THE WORLD CUP!

children.content: After the most tumultuous of years, Spain has won their first Women's World Cup!
Their players sink to the ground in joy.
They're hugging each other and crying, as you would expect.
La Roja were hugely impressive tonight - tremendous performance really.
They controlled the majority of an incredibly high-quality game and repelled everything that England threw at them.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Mary Earps gets across and makes the save! It's a poor penalty in honesty. Mary Earps gives some directional advice after gathering the ball. England will be charged up by that.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: 70' PENALTY SAVED!

children.content: Mary Earps gets across and makes the save!
It's a poor penalty in honesty.
Mary Earps gives some directional advice after gathering the ball.
England will be charged up by that.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: A long, long delay but I think probably the right decision has been made. Jenni Hermoso is stepping up. Lucy Bronze has gone over as well - so two Spanish players have gone to stop her from chatting to her. Hermoso did miss a penalty earlier in the tournament.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: 68' PENALTY SPAIN!

children.content: A long, long delay but I think probably the right decision has been made.
Lucy Bronze has gone over as well - so two Spanish players have gone to stop her from chatting to her.
